  <description><![CDATA[<p>Cefalù is one of Sicily’s true delights; a charming historical town packed with places of interest and a fine, long sandy beach. Once a traditional fishing village, the medieval centre is a maze of narrow streets where you can now find plenty of shops, restaurants and bars where you can sip a glass of Sicilian wine in the shade of a palm tree.</p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>What to see on a Cefalù holiday</strong></p>
<p>Apart from the beach, the main attraction is the Norman cathedral, which dominates the town and is decorated with glistening Byzantine mosaics. Lots of little cafés sit at its base so pull up a chair and enjoy an espresso while you admire it from the outside. </p>
<p>You'll spot La Rocca in the distance, just outside the town. This magnificent hill is perfect for an energetic walk - head to top to see some ancient ruins and get amazing views over the sea.</p>
<p>Discover more things to see and do in <a data-udi="umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344}" title="Sicily">Sicily</a>.</p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Why book a holiday in Cefalù with Inghams?</strong></p>
<p>We've got a great choice of hotels in and near Cefalù. Enjoy warm hospitality and fantastic Italian food with our hand-picked properties. Your holidays is <a data-udi="umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae" href="/{localLink:umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae}" title="In Safe Hands">in safe hands</a> with Inghams.</p>]]></description>
